D9%91%D8%B3%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dip, to plunge","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"عَنْ أَنَسِ بْنِ مَالِكٍ، قَالَ كَانَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم إِذَا صَلَّى الْغَدَاةَ جَاءَ خَدَمُ الْمَدِينَةِ بِآنِيَتِهِمْ فِيهَا الْمَاءُ فَمَا يُؤْتَى بِإِنَاءٍ إِلاَّ غَمَسَ يَدَهُ فِيهَا فَرُبَّمَا جَاءُوهُ فِي الْغَدَاةِ الْبَارِدَةِ فَيَغْمِسُ يَدَهُ فِيه","english":"Anas b. Malik reported that when Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) had completed his dawn prayer, the servants of Medina came to him with utensils containing water, and no utensil was brought in which he did not dip his hand; and sometime they came in the cold dawn (and he did not feel reluctant in acceding to their request even in the cold weather) and dipped his hand in them."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ɣa.ma.sa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n32427","headword_ar":"غَمَسٌ","root":"gms","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", [like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafaDN","text_ar":"نَفَضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manofuwDN","text_ar":"مَنْفُوضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c., or perhaps a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gamosN","text_ar":"غَمْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garosN","text_ar":"غَرْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"magoruwsN","text_ar":"مَغْرُوسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and many other instances,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Immersed, immerged, dipped, plunged,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sunk."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}